    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Sir
                                    <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Personal.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20,
                                1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir Julian</hi>: The President is desirous
                            to learn the reply of Her Majesty’s Government to the proposition
                            submitted in Department’s note of the 4th instant, to stop sealing by
                            citizens of the United States as well as by subjects of Her Majesty,
                            pending the arbitration of questions in dispute touching the seal
                            fisheries in Behring Sea.</p>
                <p>I should be glad to know as soon as possible the present state of the
                            matter.</p>
                <p>I remain, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
